Install it by running the following command in your terminal:
sudo apt-get install -y nam
sudo apt-get install -y ns2
sudo apt update

( sudo not required if you are a root user)

For X-Graph Installation:
Just Copy Paste the below lines !!

sudo apt install perl libxt-dev libx11-dev libxmu-dev
wget http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/pool/universe/x/xgraph/xgraph_12.1-17_amd64.deb
wget http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/pool/main/libx/libx11/libx11-6_1.6.4-3ubuntu0.2_amd64.deb
wget http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/pool/main/g/glibc/libc6_2.27-3ubuntu1_amd64.deb
sudo dpkg -i *.deb


To check your installation Download red.tcl file and kindy follow the steps mentioned below.
In the terminal:
Check the present working directory by typing:  pwd
Move to directory where you have downloaded red.tcl file. [ cd "directory name" ]
Now type :        ns red.tcl
Now, you can see Network simulator and x-graph working.
